## Execution model

This primitive is built through the 3-role model — **planner -> plan-review -> executor
-> execution-review**, each a separate subagent, never self-review.

- **Executor placement:** `delegate` — a single fresh subagent builds __NAME__ from a
  self-contained brief (the default placement; switch to `parallel`, `inline`, or a
  test-loop only when the task nature calls for it).
- **Evaluator:** `reviewer` — a stateless, independent reviewer vets the result before
  ship (use a `test-oracle` instead, or `both`, whenever a binary acceptance test exists).

The placement and evaluator keywords above are the load-bearing shape declaration — keep
both present so the model's gates recognize this primitive as correctly wired.

See ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/3-role-model.md — the 3-role model is the default for new primitives in this workspace.

## Role-ledger spawn snippet

When the orchestrator spawns each role subagent for __NAME__, it prepends the role tag to
the brief and records the role in the per-task ledger:

```
3ROLE_TASK:<id> ROLE:<role>
node "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/3role-ledger.mjs" append --session <sid> --task <id> --role <role> --agent <agentId>
```

At role close, append the artifact path (the overlay merges onto the spawn-time id):

```
node "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/3role-ledger.mjs" append --session <sid> --task <id> --role <role> --artifact <path>
```

